entries.meaning: (rare) Extraordinarily cosmic; that which truly transcends the very cosmos; supercosmic.
examples: Of the Gods some are of the world, cosmic, and some above the world, hypercosmic. By the cosmic I mean those who make the cosmos. Of the hypercosmic Gods some create essence, some mind, and some soul. Thus they have three orders; all of which may be found in treatises on the subject.
